          <p><strong>Specifications:</strong> 102mm aperture, 1325mm focal length, f/13 focal ratio, Maksutov-Cassegrain optical design, computerized alt-azimuth single-arm fork mount, 40,000+ object database, SkyAlign technology, included 25mm eyepiece (53x), StarPointer finder, NexStar+ hand controller, 8 AA battery power or optional AC adapter.</p>

          <p><strong>GoTo Performance:</strong> SkyAlign alignment procedure requires centering three bright celestial objects (stars or planets)—typically completed in 5-10 minutes. After alignment, hand controller locates and slews to selected objects automatically with typical accuracy within field of 25mm eyepiece. Tracking compensates for Earth's rotation keeping objects centered during observation. Database includes planets, moon, Messier objects, NGC/IC objects, and named stars. Tour mode automatically presents best visible objects for current date/time/location.</p>

